Step 1: Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio  
• Total Liabilities can be determined by subtracting Total Owner's Equity from Total Liabilities and Owner’s Equity.  
 Total Liabilities = 21737442.99 – 16099532.29 = 5637910.70  
• Total Assets = 21737442.99  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 5637910.70 / 21737442.99 ≈ 0.2593, which rounded off is approximately 0.26  

Step 2: Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
• Gross Profit = 291843.79  
• Total Revenue = 836813.79  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100% = (291843.79 / 836813.79) × 100% ≈ 34.88%  

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1919526.63  
• Total Current Liabilities = 5637910.70  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities = -1919526.63 / 5637910.70 ≈ -0.3409, which rounded off is about -0.34  

Thus, the answer in the required format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.26",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "34.88%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.34"
  }
}
